    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think the answer is C) Inertia is only for heavy objects."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Not quite, but that's okay! The correct answer is B) All objects have inertia. Inertia is a property of matter that every object possesses, regardless of its weight."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Let’s do the last question!"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Inertia is an example of: A) A force B) Energy C) A property of matter D) A type of motion"
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The answer is C) A property of matter."
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Well done! You're right, inertia is indeed a property of matter. It helps explain how objects behave in motion or at rest."
    },
    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks for the quiz. I'm all done!"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're fantastic! Keep up the great work with your studies and never hesitate to ask more questions!"
    }
  ]
}

